  		<div><h3>Comments</h3></div>
  		<div>
  			<div id="item-1773"><p>As you say, the onions are chopped way too coarsely; that&#8217;s apparent from the photo. It also looks like you used more onion than I did, but that could just be an effect of the difference in the fineness of the chopping.</p>
<p>I only use one fork for the mixing, but I do mix the crumb/onion/egg/seasoning mixture really well before adding the meat. I may mix the meat and seasonings a little more thoroughly than I indicated in the recipe; then when I shape the loaf I use a rubber spatula to help sculpt it, pressing it somewhat firmly into shape. I don&#8217;t want it too dense, but I don&#8217;t want it to crumble all over the place when I try to slice it.</p>
<p>Also, letting it sit for 5-10 minutes in a warm spot in the kitchen on the heated platter before slicing will help it firm up a little. That&#8217;s a good idea with all meat.</p></div>
